        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 11 at 6:26PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 626 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sweet Water, or 14 miles northwest of Thomasville, moving north at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thomaston, Half Acre, Sweet Water, Freddie Jones Field, Jefferson,
Old Spring Hill, Pin Hook, Octagon, Consul, Magnolia, Clayhill,
Dayton, Calvary, Wayne, Miller, Linden, Chickasaw State Park, Dixons
Mill, Myrtlewood, and Demopolis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
